## ğŸš€ Features

- ğŸ§  Trains multiple models: Linear Regression, Decision Tree, Random Forest  
- ğŸ“ˆ Tracks experiments using MLflow  
- ğŸ¯ Displays RÂ² scores for evaluation  
- ğŸ–¥ï¸ Streamlit interface for predictions  
- âš™ï¸ FastAPI backend for serving predictions  

---

## ğŸ“Š Dataset

The project uses the **bike_sharing.csv** dataset containing:

- Date & time  
- Weather conditions  
- Temperature, humidity  
- Count of bike rentals (target variable)  

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Installation

1. **Clone the repository:**

   \`\`\`bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/bike-sharing-prediction.git
   cd bike-sharing-prediction
   \`\`\`

2. **Set up a virtual environment:**

   \`\`\`bash
   python -m venv venv
   # macOS/Linux
   source venv/bin/activate  
   # Windows
   venv\Scripts\activate
   \`\`\`

3. **Install dependencies:**

   \`\`\`bash
   pip install -r requirements.txt
   \`\`\`

---

## âš™ï¸ Running the App

1. **Start the backend:**

   \`\`\`bash
   uvicorn backend.main:app --reload
   \`\`\`

2. **Start the frontend:**

   \`\`\`bash
   streamlit run frontend/app.py
   \`\`\`

---

## ğŸ“¦ Trained Models

Pre-trained models are saved as \`.pkl\` files in the \`models/\` folder. These are loaded by the backend to serve predictions.

---

## ğŸ§ª MLflow Tracking

- MLflow logs experiments and metrics.  
- To launch the MLflow UI, run:

  \`\`\`bash
  mlflow ui
  \`\`\`

---

## ğŸ“ˆ Evaluation Metrics

Models are evaluated based on:

- RÂ² Score (stored in \`models/r2_scores.json\`)  
- MAE, RMSE (optional â€” can be added for further improvements)  

